data.description:
Beautiful 3 bedrooms, 2.5 bath house with rear detached garage has lots to offer in the highly desirable Windermere area on Chase Rd! This house is on a lot right next to a well-manicured common area sidewalk that offers more space and sunlight than other lots. Open floor open, well maintained with ceramic tile and laminate floor on the first floor, carpet on the second-floor loft area and all bedrooms. A fully equipped kitchen offers 42" cabinets, granite counters and upgraded stainless steel appliances. Sliders off family room leading to the covered back patio for you to enjoy the outdoors.

All bedrooms and the laundry room are conveniently located on the second floor. The loft area is another perfect place for a family gathering. The Master bath features dual sinks and a frameless shower door. All bedroom's closets have custom-built in shelving. This house is freshly painted, professionally cleaned, and had an Ozone treatment for air purification that includes the A/C ducts.
Great Neighborhood, Great Schools & Great location! Walking distance to Sunset Park Elementary School. Windermere Landings offers a community pool, playground, a huge open park and a fenced dog park. Easy access to SR 429, Turnpike and 408. Close to Disney theme parks. Shopping, dining and attractions are all within a vibrant area. Windermere ranked number one as the best place to live for suburbanites in Florida. Must see! Call now to schedule a showing!

Applicants must have a household income 3 times more than the rent amount. No criminal and previous eviction history. Credit and background check will be conducted. First month rent and security deposit due at Lease Signing.
